whatIsATypeVariable = "types are Capitalised, when :t returns a lowercase type that means its a variable for which a type can be placed. For example the fst function returns the type of the first element in the pair, so its type is the following: (a,b) -> a"
whatDoWeCallFunctionThatUseTypeVariables = "polymorphic functions, these much not use general features of a type but remain general and they are very powerful."